 leave your users wondering how to get something they need? Perhaps their digital downloads? Maybe your site leave your users wondering how you came up with such a great design? Think about it&#8230; The [...]</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/gamifying-wordpress-e-commerce-through-the-lens-of-curiosity/\">Gamifying WordPress e-Commerce through The Lens of Curiosity</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org\">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"DanMilward\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1048:\"<p>This is a good one. You should be able to relate this to your  next WordPress project &#8211; does your site leave your users wondering how to get something they need? Perhaps their digital downloads? Maybe your site leave your users wondering how you came up with such a great design? Think about it&#8230;</p>\n<p><strong>The Lens of Curiosity  </strong></p>\n<p>To use this lens, think about your user&#8217;s true motivations &#8211; not just the goals your site has set forth and making sales, but the reason the user wants to achieve those goas. Ask yourself these questions:</p>\n<p>- What questions does my site put into the user&#8217;s mind?</p>\n<p>- What am I doing to make them care about these questions?</p>\n<p>- What can I do to make them invent even more questions?</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/gamifying-wordpress-e-commerce-through-the-lens-of-curiosity/\">Gamifying WordPress e-Commerce through The Lens of Curiosity</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org\">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"